Title: Topological Inflation
Authors: Alexander Vilenkin
Comments: 10 pages
Journal-ref: Phys.Rev.Lett. 72 (1994) 3137-3140
\\
  Inflation can occur in the cores of topological defects, where the scalar
field is forced to stay near the maximum of its potential. This topological
inflation does not require fine-tuning of the initial conditions.
